text: Tami Maida was the groundbreaking junior varsity quarterback at Philomath High School in Philomath, Oregon. In 1981, she became the first known quarterback to also become homecoming princess. After a year at Philomath, she and her family moved back to their hometown of Prince George, British Columbia. Her story was the basis of the CBS movie Quarterback Princess, with Helen Hunt as Maida. ==References== ==External links== *Football Players who were Homecoming Queens *A History of Girls Playing Tackle Football Category:High school football players in the United States Category:Canadian players of American football Category:Living people Category:Sportspeople from Prince George, British Columbia Category:Female players of American football Category:People from Philomath, Oregon Category:Year of birth missing (living people)
